  "prompt": "What is the meaning of Hindi word \u2018\u092d\u0947\u0926\u092d\u093e\u0935\u2019 (Bhedbhaav)?",
  "response": "The Hindi word **\u2018\u092d\u0947\u0926\u092d\u093e\u0935\u2019 (Bhedbhaav)** translates to **\"discrimination\"** or **\"partiality\"** in English. It refers to the unfair or prejudicial treatment of different categories of people, often based on factors such as caste, religion, gender, race, or social status. The term highlights the act of making distinctions that lead to inequality or injustice. For example, in Indian society, **\u092d\u0947\u0926\u092d\u093e\u0935** is often discussed in the context of caste-based discrimination or gender bias.",
